Wash and dry produce.

Quarter @lime{1}. Core, deseed, and dice @long green pepper{1}. Drain and rinse @black beans{1}.

In a #small bowl{}, combine @sour cream{3%tablespoon} with a big squeeze of lime juice to taste. Stir in water 1 tsp at a time until mixture reaches a drizzling consistency. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Melt @butter{1%tablespoon} in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add green pepper and cook, stirring occasionally, until softened, ~{3-4%minutes}.

Add beans and @Tex-Mex paste{1}; season with salt and pepper. Cook until beans are warmed through, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Turn off heat. Transfer to a #medium bowl{}. Wash out pan.

Place @flour tortillas{2} on a clean work surface; evenly top one half of each tortilla with @Mexican cheese blend{1%cup}. Top with filling, then sprinkle with @Monterey Jack cheese{1/4%cup}. Fold tortillas in half to create quesadillas.

Melt @butter{1%tablespoon} in pan used for filling over medium-high heat. Add quesadillas; cook until tortillas are golden brown and cheese melts, ~{2-4%minutes} per side.

> For 4 servings, you may need to work in batches, using 1 TBSP butter for each batch.

Cut quesadillas into thirds and divide between plates. Drizzle with lime crema and @hot sauce{1%teaspoon} to taste. Serve.